The mgmt generator does not emit `WireV3Options` for `ManagedServiceIdentity` serialization. This causes incorrect wire format for the `ManagedServiceIdentityType` value when `@armCommonTypesVersion` is v3, v5, or v6.

## Root Cause

The CommonTypes `ManagedServiceIdentityType` union has **different wire values per version**:

```typespec
union ManagedServiceIdentityType {
  &#34;None&#34;,
  &#34;SystemAssigned&#34;,
  &#34;UserAssigned&#34;,

  @added(Versions.v3) @removed(Versions.v4) @added(Versions.v5)
  &#34;SystemAssigned,UserAssigned&#34;,          // no space — v3, v5, v6

  @added(Versions.v4) @removed(Versions.v5)
  &#34;SystemAssigned, UserAssigned&#34;,         // with space — v4 only

  string,
}
```

The C# ARM SDK&#39;s `ManagedServiceIdentityType.SystemAssignedUserAssigned` has internal value `&#34;SystemAssigned, UserAssigned&#34;` (**v4 format, with space**). The ARM SDK&#39;s `ManagedServiceIdentity.Serialization.cs` supports a `&#34;|v3&#34;` format suffix to switch to the no-space wire format:

- `&#34;W|v3&#34;` → writes `&#34;SystemAssigned,UserAssigned&#34;` (no space, correct for v3/v5/v6)
- `&#34;W&#34;` → writes `ToString()` = `&#34;SystemAssigned, UserAssigned&#34;` (with space, correct for v4)

## How the old autorest generator detected this

The old autorest generator (`autorest.csharp`) uses `IsManagedServiceIdentityV3` in `SerializationBuilder.cs`:

```csharp
private static bool IsManagedServiceIdentityV3(InputType schema, CSharpType type)
{
    // 1. Check: C# type maps to the system ManagedServiceIdentity
    if (type is not { IsFrameworkType: false, Implementation: SystemObjectType systemObjectType }
        || systemObjectType.SystemType != typeof(ManagedServiceIdentity)
        || schema is not InputModelType objectSchema)
        return false;

    // 2. Check: the INPUT schema&#39;s &#34;type&#34; property enum contains &#34;SystemAssigned,UserAssigned&#34; (no space)
    foreach (var m in objectSchema.GetSelfAndBaseModels())
        foreach (var property in m.Properties)
            if (property is { SerializedName: &#34;type&#34;, Type: InputEnumType choice }
                &amp;&amp; choice.Values.Any(c =&gt; c.Value.ToString() == &#34;SystemAssigned,UserAssigned&#34;))
                return true;

    return false;
}
```

**Key insight:** It does NOT check `@armCommonTypesVersion` directly. Instead it inspects the **input schema** (the original spec model before type mapping) and checks if the `type` property&#39;s enum contains the no-space value `&#34;SystemAssigned,UserAssigned&#34;`. This works because:
- v3/v5/v6 specs define `&#34;SystemAssigned,UserAssigned&#34;` (no space) → matches → `WireV3Options`
- v4 specs define `&#34;SystemAssigned, UserAssigned&#34;` (with space) → doesn&#39;t match → plain `WireOptions`

When matched, autorest uses `WireV3Options` / `WireV3Options` for both serialization and deserialization of `ManagedServiceIdentity`. See `JsonCodeWriterExtensions.cs:171` and `JsonSerializationMethodsBuilder.cs:445`.

## Version → WireOptions mapping

| `@armCommonTypesVersion` | Identity type wire value | Options needed |
|---|---|---|
| v3 | `&#34;SystemAssigned,UserAssigned&#34;` (no space) | `WireV3Options` (`&#34;W\|v3&#34;`) |
| v4 | `&#34;SystemAssigned, UserAssigned&#34;` (with space) | `WireOptions` (`&#34;W&#34;`) — current default |
| v5 | `&#34;SystemAssigned,UserAssigned&#34;` (no space) | `WireV3Options` (`&#34;W\|v3&#34;`) |
| v6 | `&#34;SystemAssigned,UserAssigned&#34;` (no space) | `WireV3Options` (`&#34;W\|v3&#34;`) |

## Repro

Already reproducible in the existing mgmt test project — no new TypeSpec needed.

The test project uses `@armCommonTypesVersion(v5)` and `Foo` has `...ManagedServiceIdentityV4Property`.

**Generated code** (`FooData.Serialization.cs` line 115):
```csharp
// Current (bug): uses plain options
((IJsonModel)Identity).Write(writer, options);
```

**Expected:**
```csharp
// Should use WireV3Options for v3/v5/v6
((IJsonModel)Identity).Write(writer, ModelSerializationExtensions.WireV3Options);
```

## Suggested Fix

The new mgmt emitter/generator should replicate autorest&#39;s detection logic:

1. When the output C# type is `ManagedServiceIdentity`, inspect the **input schema** (original spec model)
2. Check if the input model&#39;s `type` property has an enum value `&#34;SystemAssigned,UserAssigned&#34;` (no space)
3. If yes, generate `WireV3Options = new ModelReaderWriterOptions(&#34;W|v3&#34;)` in `ModelSerializationExtensions` and use it for serialization/deserialization of that property
4. If no (v4 format with space), use the default `WireOptions`

Alternatively, the emitter can check the `@armCommonTypesVersion` via `getArmCommonTypesVersion(program, entity)` (exported from `@azure-tools/typespec-azure-resource-manager`) and emit `WireV3Options` for v3/v5/v6.

## Impact

- Breaks wire compatibility: sends `&#34;SystemAssigned, UserAssigned&#34;` (with space) instead of `&#34;SystemAssigned,UserAssigned&#34;` (no space) for v3/v5/v6 specs
- Causes test recording mismatches (8 failures in Storage MPG migration PR #56896)

## Related

- Storage MPG migration PR: https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/pull/56896
- Autorest detection: `autorest.csharp/src/AutoRest.CSharp/Common/Output/Builders/SerializationBuilder.cs` — `IsManagedServiceIdentityV3`
- ARM SDK v3 logic: `sdk/resourcemanager/Azure.ResourceManager/src/Common/Custom/Models/ManagedServiceIdentity.Serialization.cs`
