When generating models that inherit from a base type with additional binary data properties, the generated serialization code references a variable `additionalBinaryDataProperties0` that is never declared in the generated model class.

## Affected Models (Storage MPG Migration)

- `ListContainerItem` (`sdk/storage/Azure.ResourceManager.Storage/src/Generated/Models/ListContainerItem.Serialization.cs`)
- `FileShareItem` (`sdk/storage/Azure.ResourceManager.Storage/src/Generated/Models/FileShareItem.Serialization.cs`)

## Current Workaround

A static field is added in customization code to provide the missing variable:

```csharp
[ThreadStatic]
private static IDictionary s_additionalBinaryDataProperties0;
private static IDictionary additionalBinaryDataProperties0
    =&gt; s_additionalBinaryDataProperties0 ??= new Dictionary();
```

Note: This workaround uses `[ThreadStatic]` which does not preserve additional properties per-instance.

## Expected Behavior

The generator should declare `additionalBinaryDataProperties0` as a local variable in the deserialization method, or use the existing `_additionalBinaryDataProperties` field from the model.

## Related PR

- SDK PR: https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/pull/56896
","state":"OPEN","user":{"login":"live1206"},"labels":["Mgmt","CodeGen"],"comments":1,"created_at":"2026-03-20T06:23:46Z","updated_at":"2026-03-20T08:16:35Z"},{"number":57275,"title":"SDK Validation - .NET should only be required for the new mgmt csharp emitter, not for swagger-based generation","body":"## Problem

In TypeSpec migration PRs (e.g., [Azure/azure-rest-api-specs#41000](https://github.com/Azure/azure-rest-api-specs/pull/41000)), `SDK Validation - .NET` fails during swagger-based SDK generation and causes `SDK Validation Status` to be marked as **required and failed**, blocking the PR from merging.

### Specific Example

In [azure-rest-api-specs#41000](https://github.com/Azure/azure-rest-api-specs/pull/41000) (TypeSpec conversion for reservations):
- The PR adds TypeSpec files for the reservations service
- The `tspconfig.yaml` has **no C# emitter configuration** — only Python, Java, JS, and Go emitters are configured
- The .NET SDK (`Azure.ResourceManager.Reservations`) is still swagger-based (uses `autorest.md`, no `tsp-location.yaml`)
- SDK Validation - .NET runs and generates from swagger, which **fails**
- Because the PR has TypeSpec files, `isSpecGenSdkCheckRequired` is set to `true` for .NET management plane
- This causes `SDK Validation Status` to fail and block the PR

See comment: https://github.com/Azure/azure-rest-api-specs/pull/41000#issuecomment-4073647992

## Root Cause

The `isSpecGenSdkCheckRequired` determination in the spec repo&#39;s `spec-gen-sdk-runner` ([`getRequiredSettingValue()`](https://github.com/Azure/azure-rest-api-specs/blob/main/eng/tools/spec-gen-sdk-runner/src/command-helpers.ts)) is **too broad** for .NET:

```typescript
// eng/tools/spec-gen-sdk-runner/src/command-helpers.ts
export function getRequiredSettingValue(
  hasManagementPlaneSpecs: boolean,
  hasTypeSpecProjects: boolean,
  sdkName: SdkName,
): boolean {
  // If the SDK is azure-sdk-for-net, return false if there are no TypeSpec projects.
  if (sdkName === &#34;azure-sdk-for-net&#34; &amp;&amp; !hasTypeSpecProjects) {
    return false;
  }
  if (hasManagementPlaneSpecs) {
    return SpecGenSdkRequiredSettings[sdkName].managementPlane; // true for .NET
  }
  ...
}
```

For .NET, the check is required when `hasTypeSpecProjects = true` AND the spec is management plane. But `hasTypeSpecProjects` is determined by whether the PR has **any** TypeSpec files — it does **not** check if the TypeSpec project has a C# emitter configured (`@azure-tools/typespec-csharp`, `@azure-typespec/http-client-csharp`, or `@azure-typespec/http-client-csharp-mgmt`).

For the reservations PR:
- `hasTypeSpecProjects = true` (PR has TypeSpec files)
- `hasManagementPlaneSpecs = true` (management plane service)
- `SpecGenSdkRequiredSettings[&#34;azure-sdk-for-net&#34;].managementPlane = true`
- Result: `isSpecGenSdkCheckRequired = true` — **incorrect** because the .NET SDK has no TypeSpec generation path

## Expected Behavior

`SDK Validation - .NET` should only be **required** when the TypeSpec project uses the **new mgmt csharp emitter** (`@azure-typespec/http-client-csharp-mgmt`).

For management plane services NOT using the new mgmt emitter (still swagger-based or using older emitters), SDK Validation - .NET should be **optional** (not blocking).

## Proposed Fix

The `isSpecGenSdkCheckRequired` determination should be moved to the SDK repo&#39;s generation script, which already has the logic to detect the new mgmt emitter.

In [`Invoke-GenerateAndBuildV2.ps1`](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/main/eng/scripts/Invoke-GenerateAndBuildV2.ps1), the function `Test-MgmtSdkUsingNewGenerator` (lines 48-70) already correctly detects whether a package uses the new mgmt csharp emitter:

```powershell
function Test-MgmtSdkUsingNewGenerator {
    param(
        [string]$serviceType,
        [string]$tspConfigFile,
        [string]$sdkProjectFolder
    )
    if ($serviceType -ne &#39;resource-manager&#39;) { return $false }
    # checks tspconfig.yaml for @azure-typespec/http-client-csharp-mgmt
    # checks tsp-location.yaml for mgmt emitter package json path
    ...
}
```

### Suggested approach:
1. **In the SDK repo** (`Invoke-GenerateAndBuildV2.ps1`): Output a property like `isSpecGenSdkCheckRequired` in the generation output JSON, set to `true` only when the package uses the new mgmt emitter (per `Test-MgmtSdkUsingNewGenerator`), or for data-plane TypeSpec packages.
2. **In the spec repo** (`spec-gen-sdk-runner`): Read the SDK repo&#39;s `isSpecGenSdkCheckRequired` value from the generation output/execution report, instead of computing it from the broad `hasTypeSpecProjects` flag.

## Relevant Files

| File | Repo | Role |
|------|------|------|
| `eng/scripts/Invoke-GenerateAndBuildV2.ps1` | azure-sdk-for-net | SDK generation script with `Test-MgmtSdkUsingNewGenerator` |
| `eng/tools/spec-gen-sdk-runner/src/command-helpers.ts` | azure-rest-api-specs | `getRequiredSettingValue()` and `generateArtifact()` |
| `eng/tools/spec-gen-sdk-runner/src/types.ts` | azure-rest-api-specs | `SpecGenSdkRequiredSettings` definition |
| `.github/workflows/src/spec-gen-sdk-status.js` | azure-rest-api-specs | Reads `isSpecGenSdkCheckRequired` from artifact |","state":"OPEN","user":{"login":"live1206"},"labels":["Mgmt","bug","CodeGen"],"created_at":"2026-03-20T02:52:47Z","updated_at":"2026-03-20T16:08:42Z"},{"number":57254,"title":"[Generator Bug] ModelFactory @@flattenProperty: ProcessTypeForBackCompatibility discards flattened property values when param order changes","body":"## Bug Summary

When a model has `@@flattenProperty` applied AND the previous SDK contract had the same flattened parameters in a **different order**, the generated ModelFactory method accepts flattened parameters but passes `default` for the Properties wrapper — **silently discarding all values**.

## Root Cause

A timing/ordering issue in the generator pipeline (`CSharpGen.cs`):

1. **`EnsureBuilt()`** — factory method has `properties` wrapper param
2. **`FlattenPropertyVisitor`** — correctly replaces `properties` with flattened sub-params AND builds the ternary `new Properties(...)` in the body ✅
3. **`ProcessTypeForBackCompatibility()`** — runs **after** all visitors, detects the old SDK had the same params in a different order, calls `TryBuildMethodArgumentsForOverload` which **replaces the method body** ❌

In step 3, `ConstructMethodBody` tries to rebuild the body by matching params by name, but `&#34;properties&#34;` doesn&#39;t match any flattened param name (e.g. `&#34;provisioningState&#34;`), so it passes `default` for the Properties wrapper.

## Affected ServiceBus Models

| Model | Factory creates wrapper? | Values discarded |
|-------|--------------------------|------------------|
| `ServiceBusNamespaceData` | ✅ Correct | None |
| `ServiceBusPrivateEndpointConnectionData` | ❌ `default` | `privateEndpointId`, `connectionState`, `provisioningState` |
| `ServiceBusNamespacePatch` | ❌ `default` | `provisioningState`, `status`, `createdOn`, `updatedOn`, `serviceBusEndpoint`, `metricId`, `encryption`, `privateEndpointConnections`, `disableLocalAuth`, `alternateName` |

## Trigger Condition

The bug is triggered when:
- `@@flattenProperty` is applied to a model&#39;s `properties` field
- The old SDK (baseline) had the **exact same** flattened params in a **different order**
- No new params were added (equal count)

## Suggested Fix

In `ModelFactoryProvider.cs` method `TryBuildMethodArgumentsForOverload` (approx line 258):

`csharp
// Current: rejects equal-count reordered params
if (currentMethodParameterCount &lt;= previousParameterCount || ...)
    return false;

// Fix: change &lt;= to &lt; to allow equal-count reordering
if (currentMethodParameterCount &lt; previousParameterCount || ...)
    return false;
`

Plus use name-based parameter comparison instead of reference equality in the HashSet.

## Workaround

For `ServiceBusNamespacePatch`: reorder the `properties` field placement in the TypeSpec replacement model (move it after the `...OmitProperties&lt;&gt;` spread).

For `ServiceBusPrivateEndpointConnectionData`: the replacement model approach doesn&#39;t work because `@@alternateType` on an ARM resource strips its resource identity. Must use a Customized partial class to override the factory method.

